MoreInformation.NoteLiteral:
You will learn:

- Use various quantitative evaluation methods in project evaluation process;

- Evaluate project financial effectiveness;

- Evaluate project social – economic benefit;

- Evaluate project risk;

- Conduct a sensitivity analysis;

- Interpret results and take a decision.

The main activities during the study process will be:

- A weekly video presentation;
- Submission of practical weekly tasks;
- Independent readings;
- An intermediate (weekly) knowledge test;
- Participation in a discussion forum.

[Syllabus of the micro-module](https://uais.cr.ktu.lt/ktuis/stp_report_ects.mdl_ml?p_kodas=MM00M012&amp;p_year=2024&amp;p_lang=EN&amp;p_stp_id=)

The micro-module will be delivered in the KTU virtual learning environment. When a student is enrolled in KTU, s/he will be informed by email on how to gain access to the micro-module.  

After the successful completion of the micro-module:

- In two weeks, a student will receive an email with the link to download the ECIU University micro-credential.
- In mid-June 2025, a student from other university than KTU will receive an email with the KTU Transcript of Records that might be presented for recognition of learning outcomes at the home university.
